	<text>
		<body>
				<p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dr. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I am requested to Inform you <del>that</del> by <persName>Wm.<add>&#63;</add> Mayer</persName> &#38; <add>&#63;</add><lb/> that a packet a <del>Packet</del> was sent to you yesterday by post without date or any prelim<lb/>inary remarks&#44; the papers quite full and we were desirous to send them off without<lb/> delay.  You will perceive that neither of us are <sic>acustomed</sic> to write for the Occ<add>&#63;</add>.<lb/> yet we have ventured to express our sentiments to the best of our ability&#44; trusting<lb/> to your <sic>judgement</sic> and the kindness of your correction &#40;which you will be pleased to<lb/> make&#41; which long experience has afforded you.  <sic>be</sic> pleased to do us the justice to believe<lb/> that our motives are precisely as express in the communication sent you&#44; and above all<lb/> the desire to cause yourself as an Editor and the public to be <sic>informd</sic> of the truth of<lb/> both sides of the question.  We shall be pleased to learn from you that our<lb/> communications or any part of them will be serviceable for public information</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><sic>Doubless</sic> you are already informed that the <persName>Rev J. Rosenfelt</persName> has tendered the<lb/> resignation of his ministry&#44; which was accepted without any demur&#44; report says<lb/> the health of his family&#44; which does not agree with this climate in the cause slander says<lb/> there are other reasons&#44; it is to be hoped that the community in general will not<lb/> suffer by this sudden <hi rend="underline">change</hi>&#8212; Our new <add>Hebrew</add> is erected and under a stated<lb/> roof&#44; it is a beautiful structure&#44; and has an imposing appearance&#44; if its members<lb/> do not add <sic>concequence</sic> to it&#44; the Building certainly <hi rend="underline">has</hi> given great <sic>concequence</sic><lb/> to them&#44; the commodious vist<add>&#63;</add> room on the ground floor which is 33 by nearly 80<lb/> &#38; 15 high is nearly finished it is intended to have divine service in that room on<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> It is expected to consecrate the <add>Hebrew</add> on the coming <add>Hebrew</add>.  The Ladies<lb/> have subscribed several Hundreds of Dollars for <add>Hebrew</add> &#38; stairs carpet for the alter &#38; &#38;<lb/> A society which has been named <add>Hebrew</add> has been organized for the<lb/> purpose of <sic>ministring</sic> to the wants of the sick the Dying &#38; the dead.  They number<lb/> already of 55 persons a <add>Hebrew</add>&#8212;and <add>Hebrew</add> is attached to the society.  The first con<add>&#63;</add><lb/> for the benefit of our Jewish Hospital on Western Row&#44; comes off this Eveng at the<lb/> Melodian&#44; from the vast am&#39;t of tickets already sold it is expected the Hall will be<lb/> <sic>filld</sic> to an overflow.  I am desired by <persName>Mr. Mayer</persName> to say that he will shortly<lb/> be in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> when he will do himself the honor of calling with you<lb/> please to accept our respects and best wishes</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"> your. mo obj.</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Samuel Bruel</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>Cincin</placeName></p>
				<p><date>Jany 18 5613</date></p>
